{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:psalms.49",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "psalms",
    "chapterNumber": 49,
    "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49",
    "summary": "Source text for Psalms 49 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.49.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:1",
      "text": "Hear this, all ye people; give ear, all ye inhabitants of the world:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.49.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:2",
      "text": "Both low and high, rich and poor, together.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.49.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:3",
      "text": "My mouth shall speak of wisdom; and the meditation of my heart shall be of understanding.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.49.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:4",
      "text": "I will incline mine ear to a parable: I will open my dark saying upon the harp.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.49.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:5",
      "text": "Wherefore should I fear in the days of evil, when the iniquity of my heels shall compass me about?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.49.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:6",
      "text": "They that trust in their wealth, and boast themselves in the multitude of their riches;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.49.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:7",
      "text": "None of them can by any means redeem his brother, nor give to God a ransom for him:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.49.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:8",
      "text": "(For the redemption of their soul is precious, and it ceaseth for ever:)",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.49.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:9",
      "text": "That he should still live for ever, and not see corruption.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.49.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:10",
      "text": "For he seeth that wise men die, likewise the fool and the brutish person perish, and leave their wealth to others.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.49.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:11",
      "text": "Their inward thought is, that their houses shall continue for ever, and their dwelling places to all generations; they call their lands after their own names.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.49.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:12",
      "text": "Nevertheless man being in honour abideth not: he is like the beasts that perish.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.49.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:13",
      "text": "This their way is their folly: yet their posterity approve their sayings. Selah.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.49.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:14",
      "text": "Like sheep they are laid in the grave; death shall feed on them; and the upright shall have dominion over them in the morning; and their beauty shall consume in the grave from their dwelling.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.49.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:15",
      "text": "But God will redeem my soul from the power of the grave: for he shall receive me. Selah.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.49.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:16",
      "text": "Be not thou afraid when one is made rich, when the glory of his house is increased;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.49.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:17",
      "text": "For when he dieth he shall carry nothing away: his glory shall not descend after him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.49.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:18",
      "text": "Though while he lived he blessed his soul: and men will praise thee, when thou doest well to thyself.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.49.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:19",
      "text": "He shall go to the generation of his fathers; they shall never see light.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.49.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 49,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 49:20",
      "text": "Man that is in honour, and understandeth not, is like the beasts that perish.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
